  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "The pentose phosphate pathway (PPP) in E. coli generates NADPH for biosynthesis and ribose-5-phosphate for nucleotides. The oxidative phase (G6P \u2192 ribulose-5-P) produces 2 NADPH via Zwf and Gnd. The non-oxidative phase interconverts sugar phosphates via transketolase and transaldolase, connecting to glycolysis. The pathway has multiple branch points and can operate in different modes depending on cellular needs.",
  "id": "ecoli_pentose_phosphate_pathway",
  "keywords": [
    "pentose phosphate pathway",
    "NADPH",
    "ribose-5-phosphate",
    "Zwf",
    "transketolase"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 2,
    "not": 2,
    "or": 5
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Entry Points\n    A[Glucose-6-Phosphate] --> B{OR: Which<br/>Pathway?}\n    B -->|Oxidative PPP| C[Enter Oxidative Phase]\n    B -->|Glycolysis| D[Phosphoglucose Isomerase]\n    B -->|Both| E[Flux Split]\n    \n    %% Oxidative Phase Step 1\n    C --> F[\"Zwf: G6P Dehydrogenase\"]\n    F --> G{AND: NADP+<br/>Available?}\n    G -->|No| H[\\Enzyme Inhibited/]\n    G -->|Yes| I[6-Phosphogluconolactone]\n    I --> J[NADPH #1 Produced]\n    \n    %% Oxidative Phase Step 2\n    I --> K[\"Pgl: 6-Phosphogluconolactonase\"]\n    K --> L[6-Phosphogluconate]\n    \n    %% Oxidative Phase Step 3\n    L --> M[\"Gnd: 6PG Dehydrogenase\"]\n    M --> N{AND: NADP+<br/>Available?}\n    N -->|No| O[\\Enzyme Inhibited/]\n    N -->|Yes| P[Ribulose-5-Phosphate]\n    P --> Q[NADPH #2 Produced]\n    P --> R[CO2 Released]\n    \n    %% Branch Point\n    P --> S{OR: Cellular<br/>Need?}\n    S -->|NADPH for Biosynthesis| T[End Oxidative - NADPH Output]\n    S -->|Ribose-5-P for Nucleotides| U[Enter Isomerization]\n    S -->|Recycle to Glycolysis| V[Enter Non-oxidative Phase]\n    \n    %% Isomerization\n    U --> W[\"Rpe: Ru5P Epimerase\"]\n    W --> X[Xylulose-5-Phosphate]\n    U --> Y[\"Rpi: Ru5P Isomerase\"]\n    Y --> Z[Ribose-5-Phosphate]\n    \n    %% OR Gate: Nucleotide Synthesis\n    Z --> AA{OR: Which<br/>Nucleotide?}\n    AA -->|Purine| AB[PRPP Synthetase]\n    AA -->|Pyrimidine| AC[UMP Synthesis]\n    AA -->|Histidine| AD[Histidine Biosynthesis]\n    AB --> AE([Nucleotide Biosynthesis])\n    AC --> AE\n    AD --> AE\n    \n    %% Non-oxidative Phase\n    V --> AF[Mix of Sugar Phosphates]\n    X --> AF\n    Z --> AF\n    \n    %% Transketolase Reaction 1\n    AF --> AG[\"TktA: Transketolase\"]\n    AG --> AH[/X5P + R5P \u2192 S7P + G3P/]\n    AH --> AI[Sedoheptulose-7-P]\n    AH --> AJ[Glyceraldehyde-3-P]\n    \n    %% Transaldolase Reaction\n    AI --> AK[\"TalB: Transaldolase\"]\n    AJ --> AK\n    AK --> AL[S7P + G3P \u2192 F6P + E4P]\n    AL --> AM[Fructose-6-Phosphate]\n    AL --> AN[Erythrose-4-Phosphate]\n    \n    %% Transketolase Reaction 2\n    AN --> AO[\"/TktB: Transketolase/\"]\n    X --> AO\n    AO --> AP[E4P + X5P \u2192 F6P + G3P]\n    AP --> AQ[Fructose-6-Phosphate #2]\n    AP --> AR[Glyceraldehyde-3-P #2]\n    \n    %% Return to Glycolysis\n    AM --> AS{OR: Which<br/>Fate?}\n    AQ --> AS\n    AS -->|Lower Glycolysis| AT[Fructose-1,6-Bisphosphate]\n    AS -->|Gluconeogenesis| AU[Glucose-6-Phosphate]\n    \n    AJ --> AV{OR: Glycolysis<br/>Fate?}\n    AR --> AV\n    AV -->|Pyruvate| AW[Lower Glycolysis]\n    AV -->|Recycle| AU\n    \n    %% Operational Modes\n    AT --> AX[\"Mode 1: Max NADPH\"]\n    AU --> AY[\"Mode 2: Max Ribose-5-P\"]\n    AU --> AZ[\"Mode 3: Recycle to Glycolysis\"]\n    \n    %% Outputs\n    T --> BA([NADPH for Fatty Acid Synthesis])\n    J --> BA\n    Q --> BA\n    AW --> BB([Pyruvate to TCA])\n    AX --> BB\n    AY --> BC([Pentose Sugars])\n    AZ --> BD([Glycolytic Intermediates])\n    \n    %% Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style B fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style G fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style H fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style M fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style N fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style O fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style R fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style S fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style T fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style U fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style X fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Y fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style Z fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AA fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AB fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AD fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AG fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AO fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AR fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AS fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AT fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AU fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AV fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AY fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AZ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BA fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style BB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BD fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000",
